==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sanderling
<hw>San"der*ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Sand</ets>
+ <ets>-ling</ets>. So called because it obtains its food by searching
the moist sands of the seashore.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A small
gray and brown sandpiper (<spn>Calidris arenaria</spn>) very common on
sandy beaches in America, Europe, and Asia. Called also
<altname>curwillet</altname>, <altname>sand lark</altname>,
<altname>stint</altname>, and <altname>ruddy plover</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sanders</ent>⟦br⟧
